item.description:
The North Wind and the Sun had a quarrel about which of them was the stronger. While they were disputing with much heat and bluster, a Traveler passed along the road wrapped in a cloak.
&ldquo;Let us agree,&rdquo; said the Sun, &ldquo;that he is the stronger who can strip that Traveler of his cloak.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Very well,&rdquo; growled the North Wind, and at once sent a cold, howling blast against the Traveler.
